🚀 SETUP FOR NEW PC/LAPTOP (First Time Only)
==============================================

1. Clone the repository to your new computer:
   git clone https://github.com/Reese876/averonix.lat.git

2. Navigate to the project folder:
   cd averonix.lat

3. Verify you're connected to the repository:
   git remote -v

📝 DAILY WORKFLOW (After Setup)
===============================

Stage your changes

git add .


. stages all changes (new, modified, deleted files).

Commit your changes with a message

git commit -m "Your commit message here"


Replace "Your commit message here" with a description of your changes.

Push your changes to the remote repository

git push origin main


origin = name of your remote repository.

main = branch you are pushing to.

✅ Optional: Check status anytime:

git status

🔄 SYNC CHANGES (If working on multiple computers)
=================================================

Before starting work on any computer:
1. Pull latest changes: git pull origin main
2. Then proceed with your changes using the daily workflow above

💡 TROUBLESHOOTING
=================

If you get "not a git repository" error:
- Make sure you're in the correct folder (averonix.lat)
- Run: git init (only if starting fresh)

If you get merge conflicts:
- Run: git pull origin main
- Resolve conflicts in the files
- Run: git add .
- Run: git commit -m "Resolve merge conflicts"
- Run: git push origin main

Repository URL: https://github.com/Reese876/averonix.lat.git